narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You learn up until anti-derivatives. Pretty straightforward class. Do the homework and practice problems and the exams should be easy.
If you can place into Math 115 and you need it for a major or something, just suffer through and take it. This math course is not exciting and I'm not sure what it will do to prepare me for Math 115.
No I would not recommend it.
I felt this was a good introductory math class that you should take if you haven't taken calculus before.
Yes I would recommend it, however they must be ready to work hard to do well .

I would recommend 112 to anyone who needs an intro math class at Yale. If you work on the material on a semi-regular basis, the class isn't difficult and the lectures are interesting if you want to learn calculus.
An introduction to calculus but hard to follow even if you have prior calculus knowledge.
It is difficult and definitely not a gut class. I was worried I wouldn't pass.
Not unless the students has a very weak background in math and they have to take the class.
